			<div class="commentnumber"><a href="#c63890">30</a></div>
			<span class="authorname">Nathan Ziarek</span> said on September 28, 2009		</div>
		<div class="quote"><p>Agreed that the new design is very nice. If ever I get my act together and re-create my page, I think this will be a design that will influence my aesthetic.</p>
<p>On to being a semantic jerk, I consider "progressive enhancement" and "graceful degradation" two different things, as they explain how you tackle the problem. Do you start with the basics and then enhance or do you create the end product and then figure out where things need to fail "gracefully". I think PE is the way to go right now, since IE is in the mix. As HTML5, &lt;CANVAS&gt; and &lt;VIDEO&gt; get some major traction, though, I think we'll be able to reduce our reliance on legacy cruft and design just for modern systems. Or I hope.</p>
<p>In any case, great design!</p>
<p>nz
</p>
</div>
	</div>
