		<div class="quote"><p>I loved the faux-3D of the previous version, but this minimal design is beautiful. I remain envious of your ability to crank out redesigns, etc., at such a clip!</p>
<p>That said, it'd be neat if the little ribbons, stars, etc., <em>did</em> something. I half-expected the one next to the post title to function as a permalink (since it looks like a bookmark); the same goes for the one by the "Conversation" heading. Maybe some <code>:hover</code> and <code>:focus</code> trickery, such as the ribbon being colorized (or in the case of previous entries on the main page, the ribbon fading in to replace the star) would add a little bit of interactive pizazz?</p>
