<p>And reading through the comments, it's fascinating how polarizing a design can be - there are more than a few people that felt the previous, busier design was nicer â€” and that's more than valid. But personallyâ€”as someone who pours over design sites way too muchâ€”I often feel so inundated with busy, bright, <em>designed</em> sites that seeing something so spare and clear feels like a long, cool drink of water: refreshing and sustaining.</p>
