		<div class="comment snook" id="c63952">
		<div class="meta">
			<div class="commentnumber"><a href="#c63952">91</a></div>
			<span class="authorname">Jonathan Snook</span> said on October 02, 2009		</div>
		<div class="quote"><p>@Tom-c: I used FontForge to delete any unused glyphs and then exported as TTF, which I then used to create an EOT. I wanted to use font-face, keep file size down (Gotham is 160k in a single weight), and try to prevent it from being used on other sites. Hopefully they'll be okay with this non-commercial usage of it and the steps I went through to protect it.
</p>
</div>
	</div>
